  <!-- ### vibe: BE Honest + Relatable -->

  <AboutContent
    title="About me blurb"
    paragraph1="For a long time, I thought of myself mostly as a builder—someone who made things work. But living in Joshua Tree, surrounded by wide skies, strange plants, and creative people, something shifted. I started to see the web not just as a tool, but as a canvas."
    paragraph2="I’ve been learning how to be more creative—not just with code, but with how I think, feel, and design. I pay more attention now: to shape and space, to rhythm and flow, to how a site feels when you land on it. I study how artists express themselves, how stories are told visually, and how to make websites feel more like places than pages. "
    paragraph3="It’s a process, and I’m still growing—but that curiosity has become a core part of my work. I build with intention. I design with feeling."
    paragraph4=" And I try to leave room for a little bit of wonder in everything I make."
